"a.严重伤害的 【英】 adj. 严重伤害的(causing suffering ; hard to bear; severe) 【考】 反义词：slight(轻微 的) 【记】 griev(悲痛)+ous 【例】 The soldier received a grievous head wound. adj. 极度痛苦的; 严重伤害的; 极兇残的 = severe 【反】slight(adj 轻微的; 微小的); joyous(adj 快乐的) 【记】grieve grievous (adj.)  c.1300, from Anglo-French grevous (Old French grevos) ""heavy, hard, toilsome,"" from grief (see grief). Legal term grievous bodily harm attested from 1803."
